"what sets the two fascinating fields of anthropology and archaeology apart they may seem interchangeable and although different they are closely related simply put anthropology is the study of humanity it is a broad field that includes physical cultural and behavioral aspects of what makes us human it has a focus on both present and past to better understand factors that drive our daily experiences Archaeology is a study of former societies through the remains of their material culture data from artifacts allows us to depict a picture of our Evolution as a species and understand how people lived across space and time many archaeologists consider themselves a part of the broader discipline of anthropology through both fields we hope to provide scientific evidence of how we came to be and use that information to better guide our future "